{"title":"{{< i18n project_charter >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n project_charter >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n# Project Charter  \n\n## Subsea Benthic Analysis AI – Multi-Modal Environmental Intelligence Pipeline\n\n---\n\n## Project Identification\n\n**Project Name**  \n{{< meta project-name >}}\n\n**Sponsor**  \n{{< meta project-sponsor >}}\n\n**Product Owner (PO)**  \n{{< meta project-po >}}\n\n**Project Manager**  \nDesignated by SUB\n\n**Date**  \n[To be filled]\n\n---\n\n## Purpose and Justification\n\nThe purpose of this project is to establish an **AI-enabled environmental\nintelligence capability** to support **ecological analysis of subsea\nenvironments**, with initial focus on **automated screening of AUV imagery**.\n\nThe project addresses a critical scalability challenge: the exponential growth\nof subsea inspection data has exceeded the capacity of manual ecological\nanalysis, increasing risks related to:\n\n- Delayed environmental assessments  \n- Specialist overload  \n- Potential loss or late identification of ecologically relevant benthic\n  information  \n\nAutomation is introduced **as an enabler**, not as an end in itself, to preserve\nand strengthen ecological rigor at scale.\n\nThe strategic justification for this initiative is detailed in the **Business\nCase** (@sec-business-case).\n\n---\n\n## Strategic Alignment\n\nThis project is aligned with Petrobras Subsea (SUB) strategic drivers:\n\n- **Environmental stewardship and ecological responsibility**\n- **Digitalization of subsea inspection and monitoring**\n- **Reduction of human exposure and specialist overload**\n- **Creation of reusable digital environmental assets**\n- **Long-term sustainability of environmental analysis capabilities**\n\nThe project is executed in partnership with **NOAA (internal SUB unit)**, which\nprovides environmental validation authority.\n\n---\n\n## Objectives\n\n### Primary Objective (MVP)\n\nDevelop and validate a **binary AI-based screening capability** capable of\ndistinguishing:\n\n- Subsea imagery containing **benthic-relevant ecological features**\n- Subsea imagery that is **non-ecologically relevant** for benthic analysis\n\nThe MVP prioritizes **precision and ecological protection** over aggressive\nautomation.\n\n---\n\n### Secondary Objectives\n\n- Reduce manual ecological screening effort while preserving expert authority  \n- Shorten environmental analysis cycles for AUV campaigns  \n- Establish a scalable, offline-first AI pipeline  \n- Create reusable, auditable environmental digital assets  \n- Prepare technical foundations for future detection, segmentation, and\n  ecological intelligence use cases  \n\n---\n\n## High-Level Scope\n\n### In Scope (MVP)\n\n- Automated screening of AUV still images  \n- Batch and offline-first processing  \n- AI-assisted annotation with human-in-the-loop validation  \n- Environmental SME oversight and validation  \n- Dataset and model versioning  \n\n### Out of Scope (MVP)\n\n- Real-time or streaming deployment  \n- Full taxonomic classification  \n- Autonomous decision-making without human validation  \n- Advanced multimodal fusion beyond still imagery  \n\n---\n\n## Definition of Success (High-Level)\n\nProject success is defined by **ecological value delivery**, supported by\noperational and economic benefits.\n\nHigh-level success indicators include:\n\n- Demonstrated protection of benthic-relevant data  \n- Measurable reduction in manual screening effort  \n- Reduction in time to environmental insight  \n- Positive validation by NOAA / SUB environmental specialists  \n- Creation of reusable environmental data assets  \n\nDetailed success metrics are defined in the **OKRs → KPIs Executive Tracking**\ndocument.\n\n---\n\n## Key Risks (High-Level)\n\n- Risk of ecological data loss due to model error  \n- Annotation subjectivity and inconsistency  \n- Class imbalance in subsea imagery  \n- Adoption resistance if ecological confidence is not preserved  \n\nMitigation strategies are defined in the **Risk Register** (@sec-risk-register)\nand governed through KPI-based Stage-Gates (@sec-stage-gates).\n\n---\n\n## Governance and Decision Framework\n\nThis project follows a **Stage-Gate governance model** (@sec-stage-gates), where\nprogression is authorized only if **ecological protection KPIs meet minimum\nthresholds**.\n\nKey governance principles:\n\n- Environmental protection KPIs take precedence over efficiency KPIs  \n- Human-in-the-loop validation is mandatory  \n- No scaling decision may be taken without ecological validation  \n\nThe detailed governance model is defined in:\n- Strategy & Governance – Value Stream & OKRs  \n- OKRs → KPIs Executive Tracking  \n- Stage-Gates KPI-Based Governance  \n\n---\n\n## Authorization\n\nThis Project Charter formally authorizes:\n\n- Allocation of resources for Planning and MVP Execution  \n- Engagement of NOAA / SUB environmental specialists  \n- Initiation of AI-assisted ecological screening activities  \n\nApproval of this Charter authorizes the project to proceed according to the\ndefined governance framework.\n\n---\n\n## Approvals\n\n| Role | Name | Signature | Date |\n|-------|-------------|--------------------|----|\n| Sponsor (NOAA / SUB) | {{< meta executive-sponsor >}} | | |\n| Environmental SME Lead | {{< meta sme-lead >}}| | |\n| Project Owner | {{< meta project-po >}} | | |\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"r